<br>Karana Server
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucoray.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Coray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/01 1:20:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dain aggro management?</span><hr size=1> It's going to be harder than normal with the dain no matter what really, and it isn't even necessarily required.<br>
<br>
for 350 dain, you can get away with just dogpiling him, stuff him in a corner and beat on him, everyone doesnt 'over aggro', healers heal their own etc.  deaths depends on how well people watch aggro, and how much lag you have, usually 3-8 would be about normal.<br>
<br>
for 425 dain, on xev we've been lucky really and had a streak of 350s for months but recently we fought the 425 dain, and it was a surprise (it was 350 and then someone did the ring war).  we ended up just fighting him the same way we do the 350 and won in a bit messier fight but had around 42 people.<br>
<br>
how I would normally fight him is different.  months ago when we tried him, we used 2 main tanks, alternating as they got banished.  2-3 clerics on each etc.  you'd want all melee to be shrunk, at max range, and the main tanks to have some nice taunt weapons.  <br>
<br>
the biggest issue is the fact that he forgets you almost always when he banishes you, so it can be difficult to get aggro back easily.<br>
<br>
The difficulty with managing his aggro is a major component to his overall difficulty and I doubt theres really any easy trick around it. <p><b><a href="http://www.hec.utah.edu/~day/av/Coray/profile.html"><font
color="#FFFFFF" size="3"><sup>Coray Bloodwake</sup></font></a><br>"Accept the challenges so that you can feel the exhilaration of victory. "</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usinark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinark</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/01 12:04:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dain aggro management?</span><hr size=1> Just spend 5 minutes thinking about why it's hard to keep aggro on the MT. Once you know what the problem is, and it's pretty obvious, it's not too difficult to come up with a way around it. There are at least 3 good ways to kill him, I'm sure you can come up with one of them by yourself.<br>
